{"id":172,"parent_id":0,"book_id":8,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":172,"title":"Beard","subtitle":"","short_title":"Beard","uri":"/scriptures/bd/beard","content":[["div",{"id":"t1","uri":"/scriptures/bd/beard.t1","order":".000.466"},[".title","Beard"],["div",{"id":"p1","uri":"/scriptures/bd/beard.p1","order":".000.467"},"Regarded by the Jews as of great importance (whereas Egyptians always shaved); the trimming of the corners was forbidden (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/lev/19.26-28"},"Lev. 19:26–28"],"), such a practice being a mark of idolatry (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/jer/41.5"},"Jer. 41:5"],"). See also",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/1-sam/21.13"},"1 Sam. 21:13"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/2-sam/10.4"},"2 Sam. 10:4"],". A leper was compelled to shave (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/lev/14.9"},"Lev. 14:9"],")."]]],"refs":null}
